GP-TSM is a software package that includes original code created by the researchers listed below (the “Software”), and third-party code that may be obtained by End Users under separate terms of use. The Software is designed to summarize text by denoting word salience while preserving grammar. The Software was developed by Ziwei Gu, Ian Arawjo, Kenneth Li, Jonathan K. Kummerfeld, and Elena L. Glassman at Harvard University. It is distributed for free academic and non-commercial research use by President and Fellows of Harvard College (“Harvard”).

